@startuml
title Viaverse Team Ownership / Workstream Boundaries — Component Diagram

component "Product / Domain\nuse cases\nacceptance\nroadmap priority" as Product
component "Design / UX\nKMP screens\ndesign system\nflows/prototypes" as Design
component "Client Team\nKMP Compose\nmobile/web shared UI\nAPI integration" as Client
component "Backend Team\nSpring Boot\nbounded contexts\nports/adapters" as Backend
component "Platform/DevOps\nAWS/EKS/CI/CD\nobservability\nsecrets" as Platform
component "QA / Test\nmanual QA\nautomated tests\nrelease gates" as QA
component "Security/Privacy\nKVKK\nthreat model\npolicy review" as Security
component "Data/Search/AI\nOpenSearch\nanalytics\nmatching/AI" as Data
component "Ops/Support/Admin\nmoderation\nsupport workflows\nrunbooks" as Support
component "Docs / Architecture\nADRs\nUML\nAGENTS.md\ncoding rules" as Docs

Product --> Design : flow requirements
Design --> Client : UI contracts
Client --> Backend : API contracts
Backend --> Platform : deploy/runtime
Product --> QA : acceptance
Backend ..> Data : events/indexes
Backend ..> Security : auth/privacy
Platform ..> Security : secrets/IAM
QA --> Docs : test evidence
Support --> Docs : runbooks
Data ..> Product : quality insights

note bottom
Teams are workstreams, not silos.
Every vertical slice needs product, UX, client, backend,
data/security, QA and docs coordination.
end note
@enduml
